<section class="content-section">
    <div class="content-container">
        <div class="text-content">
            <h2 class="section-title">Mumbai Rules for Xero Users — Maharashtra PTRC/PTEC, Cloud Ledger Edit Logs</h2>
            <div class="content-text">
                
                <p>A Mumbai company on Xero registers under the Maharashtra Shops Act like any other, and its payroll carries the state's two profession-tax lines whether the ledger sits on a desktop or in the cloud. What Maharashtra does not change is the edit-log rule the platform itself has to satisfy.</p>
<p>So the audit-trail mandate reaches the cloud ledger while the state payroll runs beside it. The records must stay retrievable in India and every invoice must meet the tax-invoice rules, which is why a reconciled <a href="/glossary/accounting/multi-currency-bank-feed">Multi-Currency Bank Feed</a> and a clean edit history matter. Xero bookkeeping in Mumbai answers to the provisions below.</p>
<ul class="al-list"><li><span class="al-t"><strong>Maharashtra State Tax on Professions, Trades, Callings and Employments Act 1975</strong></span><span class="al-d">Profession tax runs on PTEC for the entity and PTRC on salaries, carried in the payroll module whatever the accounting platform.</span></li><li><span class="al-t"><strong>Rule 3(1), Companies (Accounts) Rules 2014</strong></span><span class="al-d">The cloud ledger keeps an audit trail of every change with its date, switched on all year and never disabled.</span></li><li><span class="al-t"><strong>Rule 3, Companies (Accounts) Rules 2014 with Section 128(1)</strong></span><span class="al-d">Stay accessible within India, legible and backed up, and recoverable across the eight-year retention window.</span></li><li><span class="al-t"><strong>Maharashtra Shops and Establishments Act 2017</strong></span><span class="al-d">The establishment registers under the Maharashtra Shops Act, framing the employment records behind the payroll.</span></li><li><span class="al-t"><strong>Section 31 with Rule 48, CGST Act 2017</strong></span><span class="al-d">Invoicing carries the tax-invoice fields and, above Rs 5 crore turnover, an IRN through the e-invoice portal. Full platform detail sits on the <a href="/xero-accounting">parent Xero page</a>.</span></li></ul><p style="margin-top:20px;padding-top:16px;border-top:1px solid var(--gray-200);font-size:13px;color:var(--text-muted);"><strong>Official sources:</strong> <a href="https://www.mca.gov.in" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Ministry of Corporate Affairs</a> &middot; <a href="https://www.incometax.gov.in" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Income Tax Department</a> &middot; <a href="https://www.gst.gov.in" target="_blank" rel="noopener">GST Portal</a> &middot; <a href="https://www.startupindia.gov.in" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Startup India (DPIIT)</a></p>

            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>


