                    <div class="faq-expanded__item">
  <h3 class="faq-expanded__q">Can a Mumbai private limited company legally keep its books in Xero?</h3>
  <div class="faq-expanded__a"><p>Yes, but the Companies (Accounts) Rules require books maintained in electronic mode to be backed up on servers physically located in India on a daily basis, with the service provider and server location disclosed to the Registrar. Since Xero hosts outside India, we run a scheduled daily India-side backup of the ledger export and record the disclosure, because auditors ask for evidence.</p></div>
</div>
                    <div class="faq-expanded__item">
  <h3 class="faq-expanded__q">Does Xero file GSTR-1 and GSTR-3B?</h3>
  <div class="faq-expanded__a"><p>No, Xero has no Indian GST return module, so its tax rates are mapped to GST heads inside the ledger and the return is prepared from a mapped export filed on the GST portal or through a GST Suvidha Provider. Maharashtra GSTR-3B falls due on the 22nd for turnover up to Rs 5 crore under QRMP. We lock the mapping once, then reconcile monthly.</p></div>
</div>
                    <div class="faq-expanded__item">
  <h3 class="faq-expanded__q">How are e-invoice IRNs generated when billing from Xero?</h3>
  <div class="faq-expanded__a"><p>E-invoicing applies from Rs 5 crore aggregate turnover, and because Xero cannot generate an IRN, invoices are pushed to the invoice registration portal through a connector or e-invoicing tool with the IRN and QR code written back onto the Xero invoice. The number series must stay identical across both systems, otherwise the portal rejects duplicates at the worst possible moment.</p></div>
</div>
                    <div class="faq-expanded__item">
  <h3 class="faq-expanded__q">How is Indian TDS handled when the ledger sits in Xero?</h3>
  <div class="faq-expanded__a"><p>Xero has no Indian TDS engine, so deductions under Sections 194C, 194J and 194-I are booked to dedicated liability accounts with a section-wise tracking category on every bill, and the challan and quarterly Form 26Q are built from that export. Deposit falls due by the 7th of the following month. Without tracking categories the quarterly return turns into a manual rebuild.</p></div>
</div>
                    <div class="faq-expanded__item">
  <h3 class="faq-expanded__q">Can Xero run Mumbai payroll with professional tax?</h3>
  <div class="faq-expanded__a"><p>No, Xero Payroll is not available for India, so salaries, PTRC deduction, EPF, ESI and Section 192 TDS are processed in a separate payroll system and posted into Xero as a monthly journal. Maharashtra PTEC for the entity is paid annually and PTRC monthly or annually by the previous year's liability. We reconcile the payroll control accounts to zero every month.</p></div>
</div>
                    <div class="faq-expanded__item">
  <h3 class="faq-expanded__q">Do Indian bank accounts connect to Xero automatically?</h3>
  <div class="faq-expanded__a"><p>Direct bank feeds for Indian banks are limited, so most Mumbai clients run either a supported feed, a secure file import of statements, or a third-party feed connector refreshed daily. Cash-heavy operations around Fort and the suburban high streets also need branch-wise cash accounts mapped separately. We set bank rules for recurring items so daily reconciliation takes minutes, not a month-end marathon.</p></div>
</div>
                    <div class="faq-expanded__item">
  <h3 class="faq-expanded__q">How does Xero handle foreign currency invoices from a Mumbai export desk?</h3>
  <div class="faq-expanded__a"><p>Xero revalues foreign currency balances at period end and posts the unrealised gain or loss automatically, but Indian reporting still needs AS 11 discipline and GST requires the invoice value converted to rupees at the notified reference rate. SEEPZ and BKC export desks also need FIRC matching against each invoice. We reconcile Xero's revaluation to the tax computation every quarter.</p></div>
</div>
                    <div class="faq-expanded__item">
  <h3 class="faq-expanded__q">Should a Mumbai business stay on Xero or move to Zoho Books?</h3>
  <div class="faq-expanded__a"><p>Stay on Xero when a foreign parent or investor already reports in it and multi-currency consolidation matters more than local filing, and move to Zoho Books when GST returns, e-invoicing and e-way bills need to come out of the ledger itself. QuickBooks is not an option, as it withdrew from India in 2023. We size any migration against one full year of data.</p></div>
</div>
                    <div class="faq-expanded__item">
  <h3 class="faq-expanded__q">What does Xero bookkeeping cost in Mumbai?</h3>
  <div class="faq-expanded__a"><p>The monthly retainer is driven by transaction and bank line volume, the number of currencies, whether GST return preparation and e-invoicing sit in scope, and whether prior periods need cleaning up before the first clean close. Xero's own subscription is billed by Xero and stays in your name. We quote after reviewing your chart of accounts and last reconciled month.</p></div>
</div>
                    <div class="faq-expanded__item">
  <h3 class="faq-expanded__q">Is access to a Mumbai office needed to run Xero?</h3>
  <div class="faq-expanded__a"><p>No, work runs remotely inside your Xero organisation with an adviser-level user added, and on-site attendance at BKC, Andheri or Nariman Point is arranged for audit walkthroughs or a system migration. Bills and bank statements arrive through Hubdoc or a shared folder, and you receive reconciled management accounts along with the GST working before the 10th of the following month.</p></div>
</div>
                </div>
            </div>

            
            <div class="highlight-box" style="margin-top:32px;">
                <p><strong>Quick Answers</strong></p>
                <p>Most of these books answer to two readers at once: an overseas parent reading the cloud file, and an Indian tax view of the same transactions. Patron runs both from one ledger, with a single chart of accounts, tracking categories carrying division and location, and tax rates that map cleanly to return boxes. Each.</p>

            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>


